1
00:00:02,302 --> 00:00:06,473
Netero: Do not
underestimate humans, meruem.

2
00:00:06,540 --> 00:00:09,410
- ( Meruem gasps )
- Netero: It’s meruem.

3
00:00:09,476 --> 00:00:12,212
That’s the name
your mother gave you.

4
00:00:15,482 --> 00:00:18,251
Meruem: What is this?

5
00:00:19,586 --> 00:00:22,923
Netero: Meruem,
king of the ants,

6
00:00:22,990 --> 00:00:26,193
you really don’t have
any idea, do you?

7
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:32,433
You know nothing
of the bottomless malice

8
00:00:32,499 --> 00:00:34,334
within the human heart.

9
00:00:34,401 --> 00:00:37,938
♪

10
00:00:38,005 --> 00:00:39,940
Meruem: Ah, yes.

11
00:00:40,007 --> 00:00:42,309
I see it now.

12
00:00:46,013 --> 00:00:49,617
From the very beginning,
checkmate was yours.

13
00:00:51,018 --> 00:00:51,952
♪

14
00:00:52,019 --> 00:00:53,954
( Singing in Japanese )

15
00:01:53,547 --> 00:01:56,683
Narrator: The bomb was
both cheap and compact,

16
00:01:56,750 --> 00:02:01,054
but despite this, it also
proved surprisingly lethal.

17
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:04,157
With the right technology,
it would be possible

18
00:02:04,224 --> 00:02:07,294
to mass-produce these bombs
in short time,

19
00:02:07,361 --> 00:02:11,065
making it a favorite
among dictatorships.

20
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:14,434
This, along with the peculiar
shape of the fallout cloud,

21
00:02:14,501 --> 00:02:17,304
earned this bomb
the name "miniature Rose,"

22
00:02:17,371 --> 00:02:20,474
or "the poor man’s Rose."

23
00:02:23,043 --> 00:02:26,914
In each of the 250 regions
across the world,

24
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:30,250
the Rose had blossomed
ten times over,

25
00:02:30,317 --> 00:02:34,354
consuming over 5.1 million
human lives.

26
00:02:35,422 --> 00:02:37,357
♪

27
00:03:39,253 --> 00:03:41,355
After terrorists used the bomb

28
00:03:41,421 --> 00:03:44,024
in the center
of an enemy nation’s capital,

29
00:03:44,091 --> 00:03:47,261
causing more
than 110,000 casualties,

30
00:03:47,327 --> 00:03:50,630
an international treaty
was quickly introduced

31
00:03:50,697 --> 00:03:53,533
which effectively banned
the bomb’s production.

32
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:57,104
However, over 80% of countries

33
00:03:57,171 --> 00:04:00,408
rejected the proposal
to discard the existing roses

34
00:04:00,474 --> 00:04:02,476
that had already been produced.

35
00:04:02,543 --> 00:04:07,081
This means that even today
in far too many countries,

36
00:04:07,147 --> 00:04:09,549
hundreds upon thousands of seeds

37
00:04:09,616 --> 00:04:13,386
still wait silently
for their chance to bloom.

38
00:04:17,157 --> 00:04:20,560
"Were humans really
so different from ants?"

39
00:04:20,627 --> 00:04:23,897
When netero decided
to use his last resort,

40
00:04:23,964 --> 00:04:26,400
could this thought
have crossed his mind?

41
00:04:26,466 --> 00:04:31,304
Unfortunately it was
far too late to ask.

42
00:04:39,413 --> 00:04:41,181
- ( Bomb explodes )
- ( Both gasp )

43
00:04:42,583 --> 00:04:46,053
Narrator: A plume of smoke
Rose in the distance,

44
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:50,090
followed closely by a distinct
rumbling in the air,

45
00:04:50,157 --> 00:04:54,695
and, in an instant, they both
knew exactly what this meant.

46
00:05:00,634 --> 00:05:03,971
At the same time,
outside of the palace

47
00:05:04,037 --> 00:05:07,440
pouf’s segment found itself
looking knuckle in the eye.

48
00:05:09,343 --> 00:05:10,444
( Knuckle gasps )

49
00:05:14,281 --> 00:05:16,650
After his experience with youpi,

50
00:05:16,717 --> 00:05:18,886
knuckle hoped
that he would be able

51
00:05:18,952 --> 00:05:21,288
to reach a similar understanding
with pouf,

52
00:05:21,355 --> 00:05:23,891
but his hopes,
faint as they were,

53
00:05:23,957 --> 00:05:26,226
were utterly shattered.

54
00:05:43,644 --> 00:05:45,379
( Knuckle sighs )

55
00:05:45,445 --> 00:05:47,681
Knov: The king can
just wave his hand

56
00:05:47,748 --> 00:05:50,284
and turn all of them
into evil spawn.

57
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:52,586
♪

58
00:05:52,653 --> 00:05:53,988
Knuckle: I see.

59
00:05:54,054 --> 00:05:55,589
Pouf’s real body
must have learned

60
00:05:55,656 --> 00:05:57,491
that something happened
to the king.

61
00:05:58,759 --> 00:06:00,628
Then the segment’s face
transformed,

62
00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:02,629
revealing its true nature.

63
00:06:03,997 --> 00:06:06,600
Did the chairman
defeat the king?

64
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:10,337
Well, I suppose
it doesn’t matter either way.

65
00:06:14,608 --> 00:06:16,877
Narrator: When he looked
at pouf’s face,

66
00:06:16,944 --> 00:06:19,213
he saw something
he did not expect,

67
00:06:19,279 --> 00:06:22,182
an insurmountable barrier.

68
00:06:26,954 --> 00:06:28,155
( Ikalgo gasps )

69
00:06:28,222 --> 00:06:29,957
It’s destroyed.

70
00:06:31,625 --> 00:06:33,393
Is everyone okay?

71
00:06:40,234 --> 00:06:42,169
( Grunting )

72
00:06:45,639 --> 00:06:46,607
( Gasps )

73
00:06:46,673 --> 00:06:49,376
( Wind blowing )

74
00:06:51,378 --> 00:06:53,413
This is brutal.

75
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:57,651
It only took them 30 minutes
to wreck the whole place.

76
00:07:00,254 --> 00:07:02,923
( Rumbling )

77
00:07:06,994 --> 00:07:08,596
Yah!

78
00:07:14,268 --> 00:07:17,037
That was close.

79
00:07:17,104 --> 00:07:18,205
Killua: Ikalgo.

80
00:07:18,272 --> 00:07:19,974
( Ikalgo gasps )

81
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:23,610
Eh? Killua!

82
00:07:25,612 --> 00:07:27,247
♪

83
00:07:27,314 --> 00:07:29,216
( Gasps )

84
00:07:35,956 --> 00:07:38,225
It’s palm.

85
00:07:39,993 --> 00:07:42,229
I see. I’m glad you’re here.

86
00:07:43,330 --> 00:07:45,365
You finally made it back to us.

87
00:07:45,432 --> 00:07:48,368
Now do you remember the plan?

88
00:07:48,435 --> 00:07:50,971
I’ll take you
to the capital by car.

89
00:07:51,038 --> 00:07:52,406
Killua: No. It turns out

90
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,274
- she wants to stay.
- Ikalgo: Oh?

91
00:07:54,341 --> 00:07:56,910
Killua: Well, she ought
to be pretty useful

92
00:07:56,977 --> 00:07:58,512
in a fight at least.

93
00:07:58,579 --> 00:08:03,417
I mean, in terms of sheer power,
she’s got me beat, probably.

94
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:05,518
( Ikalgo gasps )

95
00:08:05,586 --> 00:08:09,423
Palm: To be honest, I want
to see gon as soon as possible,

96
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:13,593
but no, I can wait.

97
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:17,097
I should be respectful
of his wishes.

98
00:08:17,164 --> 00:08:18,632
Ikalgo: His wishes?

99
00:08:18,699 --> 00:08:23,404
Killua: Thing is he’s gonna
fight pitou all by himself.

100
00:08:25,038 --> 00:08:28,108
Gon: I’ll wait right here
for one hour.

101
00:08:29,443 --> 00:08:31,345
Killua: And once
he’s made up his mind,

102
00:08:31,411 --> 00:08:33,146
he won’t budge.

103
00:08:33,213 --> 00:08:37,384
But to be honest,
that situation is ideal.

104
00:08:37,451 --> 00:08:40,054
It gives us the best chance
for a victory,

105
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:43,390
and that means
that all we can do right now

106
00:08:43,457 --> 00:08:45,492
is try to stay out of his way.

107
00:08:45,559 --> 00:08:48,128
Ikalgo: Well, sure,
but what if he--

108
00:08:48,195 --> 00:08:50,264
killua: Yeah. Yeah, I know.

109
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:54,367
If gon’s in trouble, we’ll all
rush in to help him out.

110
00:08:54,434 --> 00:08:57,537
Let’s just be ready
for whatever happens with him.

111
00:09:00,174 --> 00:09:05,112
Ikalgo: Oh, I get it. So that’s
what staying means, huh?

112
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:10,350
Even if gon uses all the power
he has right now,

113
00:09:10,417 --> 00:09:11,852
it won’t be enough.

114
00:09:11,919 --> 00:09:14,388
He still won’t be able
to beat pitou.

115
00:09:14,454 --> 00:09:17,857
In fact, even if
all three of us join him,

116
00:09:17,925 --> 00:09:19,960
pitou still has us outmatched

117
00:09:20,027 --> 00:09:23,063
and knows that
just as well as we do.

118
00:09:24,398 --> 00:09:29,103
To stay together
means we die together.

119
00:09:29,169 --> 00:09:31,338
♪

120
00:09:35,442 --> 00:09:38,011
Killua: We’re gonna look
for knuckle and the others.

121
00:09:38,078 --> 00:09:39,046
You coming?

122
00:09:39,112 --> 00:09:41,014
Ikalgo: Absolutely.

123
00:09:43,116 --> 00:09:45,619
Killua: Okay. Let’s go.

124
00:09:55,295 --> 00:09:57,998
Knuckle: We separated the king
and the royal guards

125
00:09:58,065 --> 00:10:00,134
to let the chairman
handle the king.

126
00:10:01,235 --> 00:10:03,237
It’s like Mr. Knov said.

127
00:10:03,303 --> 00:10:06,173
We completed the mission
we were assigned.

128
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:10,177
We’ll each have to decide
where we go from here.

129
00:10:10,244 --> 00:10:13,948
Do we stop or keep going?

130
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:27,194
As for me,
i’m gonna keep fighting ’em.

131
00:10:27,261 --> 00:10:31,198
I’ve already laid down my life
here more than once.

132
00:10:31,265 --> 00:10:34,335
Even if we can’t reach
an understanding,

133
00:10:34,401 --> 00:10:37,971
i’ll keep fighting
until i’m satisfied.

134
00:10:59,793 --> 00:11:01,695
♪

135
00:11:01,695 --> 00:11:02,596
♪

136
00:11:31,291 --> 00:11:32,492
Gon: You’re done, right?

137
00:11:32,559 --> 00:11:34,061
( Neferpitou gasps )

138
00:11:41,435 --> 00:11:43,637
Why did he say that?

139
00:11:43,704 --> 00:11:46,507
There’s still time.
The hour isn’t up yet.

140
00:11:46,573 --> 00:11:50,277
How could he have known
that i’d finished the surgery?

141
00:11:51,578 --> 00:11:55,415
I made sure to hide
my progress from him.

142
00:11:55,482 --> 00:11:57,985
I may have relaxed a bit,

143
00:11:58,051 --> 00:11:59,419
and if he noticed,

144
00:11:59,486 --> 00:12:02,322
then in that instant...

145
00:12:03,891 --> 00:12:05,426
(In memory)
I have to kill him...

146
00:12:06,593 --> 00:12:08,361
No matter the cost.

147
00:12:08,428 --> 00:12:13,833
I must for the king’s sake.

148
00:12:15,302 --> 00:12:17,371
Did he sense my bloodlust then?

149
00:12:17,437 --> 00:12:19,339
Gon: Okay, get up.

150
00:12:19,406 --> 00:12:21,942
( Neferpitou gasps )

151
00:12:39,126 --> 00:12:41,862
Gon: It’s time for us
to go to peijing.

152
00:12:41,929 --> 00:12:44,465
It’ll be a lot faster
if we run there.

153
00:12:45,666 --> 00:12:48,169
( Komugi whimpering )

154
00:12:56,543 --> 00:12:58,979
What happened to me?

155
00:13:00,948 --> 00:13:03,551
Neferpitou: I would like to--
komugi--

156
00:13:03,617 --> 00:13:06,286
gon: Next time
you speak out of line,

157
00:13:06,353 --> 00:13:08,021
I promise i’ll kill her.

158
00:13:10,557 --> 00:13:12,859
Komugi: I-i’m sorry!

159
00:13:12,926 --> 00:13:16,463
I’m so rude. Am I interrupting?

160
00:13:16,530 --> 00:13:19,033
Oh, forgive me,

161
00:13:19,099 --> 00:13:22,436
but I don’t think
I understand what’s going on.

162
00:13:27,407 --> 00:13:30,043
Neferpitou: I understand.
Let’s go.

163
00:13:34,581 --> 00:13:38,485
Narrator: Pitou was close enough
to decapitate gon with one arm,

164
00:13:38,552 --> 00:13:41,488
yet couldn’t move.

165
00:13:41,555 --> 00:13:45,926
After sensing how sharp
gon’s intuition was,

166
00:13:45,993 --> 00:13:48,262
pitou’s instincts kicked in.

167
00:13:49,530 --> 00:13:52,066
Neferpitou:
I can’t make a move now.

168
00:13:52,132 --> 00:13:56,103
There will be plenty of chances
on our way to the capital.

169
00:13:56,170 --> 00:14:01,409
Even so, I still have
to get komugi to the king.

170
00:14:02,509 --> 00:14:03,810
( Gasps )

171
00:14:13,053 --> 00:14:16,557
Knuckle: Gon, want me to use
chapter seven bankruptcy?

172
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:20,194
Oh, and if pitou
tries to run away,

173
00:14:20,260 --> 00:14:21,595
i’m a great tracker.

174
00:14:21,662 --> 00:14:23,197
If it gets violent,

175
00:14:23,263 --> 00:14:26,233
a.p.r. Will shield you.
Don’t worry.

176
00:14:27,901 --> 00:14:30,404
( Neferpitou gasps )

177
00:14:30,470 --> 00:14:32,405
( Komugi whimpering )

178
00:14:36,410 --> 00:14:38,012
Gon: Thanks a lot, knuckle,

179
00:14:38,078 --> 00:14:40,414
but it’s okay.

180
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:43,616
For some reason,
I trust pitou.

181
00:14:43,684 --> 00:14:45,419
( Neferpitou gasps )

182
00:14:45,485 --> 00:14:47,620
Gon: So do me a favor, knuckle.

183
00:14:47,688 --> 00:14:51,625
Take care of that girl for us
until we see kite.

184
00:14:51,692 --> 00:14:53,627
( Neferpitou gasps )

185
00:14:53,694 --> 00:14:58,032
Komugi: Uh, are you guys
talking about me?

186
00:14:58,098 --> 00:15:00,000
♪

187
00:15:11,044 --> 00:15:12,946
( Gasps )

188
00:15:14,214 --> 00:15:16,283
Neferpitou:
Does he seriously plan to...

189
00:15:16,350 --> 00:15:19,253
Knuckle: Use the girl
as a hostage?

190
00:15:23,156 --> 00:15:26,593
Gon: Once pitou heals kite,
we’ll release her.

191
00:15:26,660 --> 00:15:28,529
I promise you that.

192
00:15:28,595 --> 00:15:30,831
So I guess that means, for now,

193
00:15:30,898 --> 00:15:32,867
you’re just gonna
have to trust me, too...

194
00:15:34,268 --> 00:15:36,337
Right, pitou?

195
00:15:57,324 --> 00:15:59,326
Ikalgo: You’re sure, killua?

196
00:16:00,527 --> 00:16:02,462
You don’t want to go with gon?

197
00:16:02,529 --> 00:16:04,398
We were--

198
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:08,101
no. Killua was prepared
to die with gon,

199
00:16:08,168 --> 00:16:10,404
and even though
he knew that was the case,

200
00:16:10,470 --> 00:16:12,439
gon was so dismissive.

201
00:16:16,043 --> 00:16:19,313
Gon: It’s fine.
Leave the rest to pitou and me.

202
00:16:21,215 --> 00:16:24,585
Killua: It’s okay. That was
always the plan, wasn’t it?

203
00:16:24,651 --> 00:16:28,388
Truth is, I feel better
after hearing what he’s doing.

204
00:16:28,455 --> 00:16:30,991
Knuckle: What, like about
the hostage, you mean?

205
00:16:31,058 --> 00:16:34,828
Killua: Yeah. If I went along,
it’d be pretty risky.

206
00:16:34,895 --> 00:16:36,997
Pitou might ambush
and capture me,

207
00:16:37,064 --> 00:16:38,999
and the last thing
we want right now

208
00:16:39,066 --> 00:16:40,601
is a hostage situation.

209
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:41,601
( Knuckle gasps )

210
00:16:41,668 --> 00:16:44,471
You’ve gotta be kidding me.

211
00:16:44,538 --> 00:16:46,407
How many bloodbaths
did they have to endure

212
00:16:46,473 --> 00:16:48,608
to start thinking like that?

213
00:16:48,675 --> 00:16:49,910
Ikalgo: Uh...

214
00:16:49,977 --> 00:16:51,212
Palm: It’s all right.

215
00:16:51,278 --> 00:16:54,014
Now that i’ve
laid my eyes on gon,

216
00:16:54,081 --> 00:16:57,518
if something happens,
i’ll know about it immediately.

217
00:16:57,584 --> 00:17:01,555
Killua: Besides it’s not like
pitou is gonna abandon her,

218
00:17:01,622 --> 00:17:05,126
which means that gon
is safe for now.

219
00:17:06,226 --> 00:17:08,128
( Men sigh )

220
00:17:10,097 --> 00:17:11,899
( Komugi thinking )
What’s happening?

221
00:17:11,965 --> 00:17:14,167
I don’t understand
what’s going on here.

222
00:17:14,234 --> 00:17:17,471
I want to see dear leader.

223
00:17:17,538 --> 00:17:21,809
Where is he,
and who are these people?

224
00:17:26,413 --> 00:17:28,348
♪

225
00:17:34,388 --> 00:17:36,323
( Fire crackling )

226
00:17:44,464 --> 00:17:47,434
Narrator: The heat
of the explosion was so intense

227
00:17:47,501 --> 00:17:49,603
that it melted the rock
into magma,

228
00:17:49,670 --> 00:17:53,841
leaving a scene resembling
the mouth of an active volcano,

229
00:17:53,907 --> 00:17:58,412
a perpetual cloud of black smoke
driving all life away.

230
00:17:58,478 --> 00:18:00,413
( Shaiapouf gasping )

231
00:18:08,622 --> 00:18:09,957
Menthuthuyoupi: Hey, pouf!

232
00:18:10,023 --> 00:18:11,424
( Shaiapouf gasps )

233
00:18:13,026 --> 00:18:15,795
Menthuthuyoupi:
I’ll start searching inside.

234
00:18:15,863 --> 00:18:17,465
You look around out here.

235
00:18:17,531 --> 00:18:21,135
It’s possible the explosion
may have sent the king flying.

236
00:18:23,203 --> 00:18:26,473
You know, I was wrong.

237
00:18:26,540 --> 00:18:29,977
We’ll kill every one of them...

238
00:18:30,043 --> 00:18:31,945
By the king’s side.

239
00:18:33,447 --> 00:18:36,083
Not a single one
will be spared.

240
00:18:36,149 --> 00:18:38,084
( Shaiapouf gasping )

241
00:18:38,151 --> 00:18:40,086
♪

242
00:19:00,908 --> 00:19:02,810
- ( Menthuthuyoupi grunting )
- ( Flesh popping )

243
00:19:15,088 --> 00:19:17,057
♪

244
00:19:27,634 --> 00:19:30,137
( Segments gasping )

245
00:19:32,639 --> 00:19:34,541
Sire!

246
00:19:38,011 --> 00:19:38,945
( Gasps )

247
00:19:48,222 --> 00:19:50,357
( Menthuthuyoupi groans )

248
00:20:05,973 --> 00:20:07,408
( No audible scream )

249
00:20:07,474 --> 00:20:10,410
( Menthuthuyoupi wails )

250
00:20:10,477 --> 00:20:12,579
( Segment gasps )

251
00:20:18,485 --> 00:20:20,220
( No audible scream )

252
00:20:20,287 --> 00:20:24,024
Narrator: Youpi’s howl was not
a sign of good things to come,

253
00:20:24,091 --> 00:20:28,028
and before he
